			<h3>Press Release, 27th Mar 2015</h3>

			<p>Most General Election Hustings will happen on Thursday 23rd April</p>

			<p style="font-style: italic;">Press release for immediate release</p>

			<p>MOST General Election Hustings will happen on Thursday 23rd April, predicts MeetYourNextMP.</p>

			<p>MeetYourNextMP is a website that lists hustings events happening for the general election. Voters can easily look up events in their seat and go and question their candidates.</p>

			<p>With a total of 425 events listed across 200 seats, Thursday 23rd April is emerging as the most popular day for hustings with 27 events.</p>

			<p>MeetYourNextMP gets details of events by allowing candidates and members of the public to list hustings events around the country. This is the same “crowd sourcing” process that sites like Wikipedia use.</p>

			<p>MeetYourNextMP is supported by Democracy Club, who are a non-partisan group who work around elections. They also work on a list of candidates, an archive of election leaflets and a repository of candidates CVs.</p>

			<p>James Baster from MeetYourNextMP said: “We’d like to encourage all voters to get out to an event where they can hear from their candidates before making up their mind, whether on the 23rd or any other day! We would like to make hustings feel accessible to everyone and the first thing to do is make it easy to find out when they are on.”</p>

